{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"410efe9e-f8d0-4109-bd99-c930dfc4afc4","content":"The project directory doesn't exist yet in this workspace, but I can tell you exactly what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a dotnet tool to NuGet.org:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Mark as a dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet package metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n\n  <!-- Must be exe for stdio transport -->\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** — tells `dotnet pack` to produce a tool package.\n- **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command name users type after installing.\n- **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — required for stdio transport since the host launches the process.\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install --global MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server          # runs via stdio\n```\n\nThat's the minimum configuration. Optional additions: `PackageReadmeFile`, `PackageIcon`, `RepositoryUrl`, and `PackageTags` (e.g., `mcp;ai;tool`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"83e3d9a7-e4b3-401c-b625-914853847d6d","outputTokens":512,"requestId":"CBC2:350962:18D2AB8:1C0DF04:69FE89EF"},"id":"54591a5d-14b0-4866-9f26-3f4781622ffa","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:12:25.167Z","parentId":"c32b192e-73d0-4229-84d6-39e943e6623c"}
